step_data.thought:
I'm trying to access the Braintree Virtual Terminal, but I encountered an error when attempting to click the 'OK' button on the attention dialog. The error message indicates that there's a loading mask (with ID [146]) that's intercepting pointer events, preventing me from clicking the button. This suggests the page is still loading or processing something.

Looking at the current page, I can see that I am already on the Braintree Virtual Terminal page (as indicated by the heading 'Braintree Virtual Terminal'). There's an attention dialog showing that the Braintree Payments account needs to be configured before using the virtual terminal.

Since I can't click the OK button due to the loading mask, I should wait for the page to finish loading. The noop action will allow me to wait for a moment, giving the page time to complete any background processes.
